* Remotion is a React-based video generation library.
  ðŸ‘‰ It lets you create videos using React components instead of traditional video-editing tools.



* Using the interpolate() function to create a "fade in text animation":

    import { interpolate } from "remotion";

    const opacity = interpolate(frame, [0, 60], [0, 1], {
      /*                        ^^^^^   ^^^^^    ^^^^
      Variable to interpolate ----|       |       |
      Input range ------------------------|       |
      Output range -------------------------------|  */
      extrapolateRight: "clamp",
    });



* Frame-based animation (useCurrentFrame)

        import { useCurrentFrame } from "remotion";
        
        export const MyVideo = () => {
          const frame = useCurrentFrame();
        
          return (
            <div style={{ opacity: frame / 30 }}>
              Fade In Text
            </div>
          );
        };

* Development preview : "npx remotion preview"

* Render video (MP4) :  "npx remotion render src/index.ts MyVideo out.mp4"

* Render HLS (used in production apps) : "npx remotion render src/index.ts MyVideo out.m3u8"



* Creating a basic Remotion app ==========

  - npx create-video my-remotion-app
  
  - Understand this folder structure:
        my-remotion-app/
         â”œâ”€â”€ src/
         â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ index.ts        â† entry point
         â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Root.tsx        â† compositions live here
         â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Composition.tsx â† your video component
         â”œâ”€â”€ package.json
         â””â”€â”€ tsconfig.json

  - Entry file (src/index.ts):
          import { registerRoot } from "remotion";
          import { Root } from "./Root";
          
          registerRoot(Root);

  - Define a video composition (src/Root.tsx)
                import { Composition } from "remotion";
                import { MyVideo } from "./Composition";
                
                export const Root = () => {
                  return (
                    <>
                      <Composition
                        id="MyVideo"
                        component={MyVideo}
                        durationInFrames={150}
                        fps={30}
                        width={1920}
                        height={1080}
                      />
                    </>
                  );
                };

  - Create the video component (src/Composition.tsx)
            import { useCurrentFrame } from "remotion";
            
            export const MyVideo = () => {
              const frame = useCurrentFrame();
            
              return (
                <div
                  style={{
                    flex: 1,
                    backgroundColor: "black",
                    color: "white",
                    fontSize: 80,
                    display: "flex",
                    alignItems: "center",
                    justifyContent: "center",
                  }}
                >
                  Frame: {frame}
                </div>
              );
            };

  - Preview the video: "npm start"

  - Render the video (MP4): npx remotion render src/index.ts MyVideo out.mp4

  - Play rendered video in React app: <video src="/out.mp4" controls />





